373
00:21:36.480 --> 00:21:40.240
samples. Still, it doesn't show the transfer, but it's suggesting it.

374
00:21:40.960 --> 00:21:44.820
So we moved forward and with Dr. Ayala, he

375
00:21:44.860 --> 00:21:47.920
performed a clinical trial on human prostate

376
00:21:48.560 --> 00:21:52.480
patient samples where patients were injecting

377
00:21:52.540 --> 00:21:55.760
Botox on one side of the prostate when the other side was

378
00:21:56.420 --> 00:21:59.560
injected with saline. So each patient was his own control.

379
00:22:00.150 --> 00:22:04.040
And we looked at the mitochondrial load into cancer cells in both the

380
00:22:04.060 --> 00:22:06.720
Botox-denervated versus the saline-treated

381
00:22:08.380 --> 00:22:09.380
side of the prostate

382
00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:13.960
cancer. And what we found is when you denervate the

383
00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:17.660
cancer in human, you indeed see a decrease on the mitochondrial

384
00:22:17.920 --> 00:22:21.800
content on the cancer cells on the denervated side of the

385
00:22:21.840 --> 00:22:22.140
