386
00:22:23.450 --> 00:22:27.300
So to demonstrate the transfer in vivo, we had to move to a murine model,

387
00:22:27.340 --> 00:22:31.240
and basically, we took advantage of a mutation on the mitochondrial

388
00:22:31.319 --> 00:22:34.840
DNA, which is located for the 41 cell lines.

389
00:22:35.060 --> 00:22:39.020
Actually, this cell line is isogenic for the balb c mice, but those

390
00:22:39.060 --> 00:22:42.280
are more like a C mutation. And we used that, developed a

391
00:22:43.460 --> 00:22:46.560
quick nanopore sequencing pipeline, and basically, we

392
00:22:46.600 --> 00:22:49.500
injected the cancer cells into the animals.

393
00:22:49.540 --> 00:22:53.200
And after the tumor onset, we isolated the cancer cells and checked

394
00:22:53.280 --> 00:22:57.160
for the presence of non-mutated mitochondrial DNA into the

395
00:22:57.200 --> 00:23:01.180
